# Snyk (https://snyk.io) policy file
version: v1.25.1
ignore:
  'snyk:lesson:javascript/PT':
    - 'writer/routes/plugin-actions.ts':
        reason: >
          False positive. The flagged taint flows from the request body's
          `series`/`story` fields to `Deno.readDir(storyDir)` inside
          `writer/lib/story-chapter-io.ts:listChapterFiles`. The `storyDir`
          is computed by `validateAndResolveStoryDir()` (writer/routes/
          plugin-actions-validation.ts:138) which (a) requires both inputs to
          satisfy `isValidParam` (strict kebab/segment regex) and (b) calls
          `deps.safePath(series, story)` — the engine's containment-checked
          path resolver that returns null when the resolved path escapes
          the configured story root. Snyk's taint analysis does not recognise
          `safePath()` as a sanitiser. The directory passed to `Deno.readDir`
          is therefore provably inside the story root.
        expires: 2099-01-01T00:00:00.000Z
